FAQs
1. What are the benefits of study medicine in Malaysia?

Studying medicine in Malaysia offers high-quality education, affordable tuition fees, modern facilities, and a multicultural environment.

2. Are Malaysian medical degrees recognized internationally?

Yes, medical degrees from Malaysian universities are recognized by major medical councils worldwide.

3. What is the cost of studying medicine in Malaysia?

The cost varies by university, but it is generally more affordable compared to Western countries. This includes both tuition fees and living expenses.

4. What is the duration of a medical degree in Malaysia?

A medical degree in Malaysia typically takes five to six years to complete, including pre-clinical and clinical training.

5. How can I apply to study medicine in Malaysia?

The application process involves submitting academic transcripts, standardized test scores, and letters of recommendation. Some universities may require an entrance exam or interview.
